        "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  Please fill in each section completely. Thank you!\r\n-->\r\n\r\n### 🔎 Search Terms\r\n\r\nsymbol property constructor 2564\r\n\r\n### 🕗 Version & Regression Information\r\n\r\n- This changed between versions 4.6.4 and 4.7.4\r\n\r\n### ⏯ Playground Link\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  A link to a TypeScript Playground \"Share\" link which shows this behavior\r\n\r\n  The TypeScript Workbench can be used for more complex setups, try\r\n  https://www.typescriptlang.org/dev/bug-workbench/\r\n\r\n  As a last resort, you can link to a repo, but these will be slower for us to investigate.\r\n-->\r\n[Playground link with relevant code](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play?ts=5.1.0-dev.20230401#code/MYewdgzgLgBNCGYAm8A24CmBlAngWwCMRUYBeGXQ4gCgCIFk1NaBKAbgCgPhV4IIK+IqgDCvfjADeHGLLhR4UAJbAYAJwzwk4VDnmKVlYWUFVUdBMuCtOAXy5KwUDGoBm8YBhgBJABLwAN2whYgFpORgAbQYUdDBgswBdAC4YMABXQhdOCMijYjE+CAA6S0MQ1BS0zIJsjntucQF-IIAFNRAABxcoHG8wJWU0JQAvDCR81AElPE7UDDwMJwE-QIThMJk5aIVGOPXiRJMARhztycL+UoUrSaPyACY7Lh4imBaMAHkgtTUlJCQS0mAgwAA9nMhmmt2l0en0BkNUKNxsCpFtZKBIFA1OlgFAQGpqCw0REIhB0t1Cex0aSoAALJQQHaIWKYO4mADMZ1JMHpjLyFUuJTKwHZ5AALNyYPYGq8JB8ROBoDi8QT+oMlMMxhMKtNZvNFssfB9UeFtjEmPE7qkMlk1FKBWYhdcDKKKlVbbV7TTMcrcfiqSSebyGUyLfsxTAuTSInymRcmi7bu6TJKaTKOEA)\r\n\r\n### 💻 Code\r\n\r\n<!-- Please post the relevant code sample here as well-->\r\n```ts\r\nconst standaloneSymbol = Symbol(\"standalone\");\r\n\r\nclass SymbolClass {\r\n    static readonly staticSymbol = Symbol(\"static\");\r\n}\r\n\r\ninterface IHaveSymbols {\r\n    [standaloneSymbol]: number;\r\n    [SymbolClass.staticSymbol]: number;\r\n}\r\n\r\nclass HavePropertyInitializedSymbols implements IHaveSymbols {\r\n    [standaloneSymbol] = 1;\r\n    [SymbolClass.staticSymbol] = 2;\r\n}\r\n\r\nclass HaveOverriddenSymbols extends HavePropertyInitializedSymbols {\r\n    constructor() {\r\n        super();\r\n        this[standaloneSymbol] = 3;\r\n        this[SymbolClass.staticSymbol] = 4;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nclass HaveConstructorInitializedSymbols implements IHaveSymbols {\r\n    [standaloneSymbol]: number;\r\n    [SymbolClass.staticSymbol]: number;\r\n    constructor() {\r\n        this[standaloneSymbol] = 3;\r\n        this[SymbolClass.staticSymbol] = 4;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### 🙁 Actual behavior\r\n\r\n<!-- What happened, and why it was wrong -->\r\n\r\n```\r\nProperty '[SymbolClass.staticSymbol]' has no initializer and is not definitely assigned in the constructor.(2564)\r\n(property) SymbolClass.staticSymbol: typeof SymbolClass.staticSymbol\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt's wrong because the property is definitely assigned in the constructor\r\n\r\n### 🙂 Expected behavior\r\n\r\n<!-- What you expected to happen instead, and why -->\r\n\r\nNo error, because the property is definitely assigned in the constructor",
